{"author":"Iso Tester","data":{"body":"## S6 implemented + APPLY-PROVE-ROLLBACK on the live navapbc/rebar repo — 2026-06-30 (commit c4a8be68)\n\nPer the chosen scope (apply, prove, then roll back) — the live repo is back to its ORIGINAL state; no permanent change.\n\n**IaC (infra/terraform-github/):** two `github_repository_ruleset` (branch `main`: rules update+deletion+non_fast_forward; tags `refs/tags/**`: creation+update+deletion), DeployKey-only bypass (`actor_type=DeployKey, bypass_mode=always`, NO actor_id — sending null is API-rejected), provider `integrations/github >=6.8.0` (resolved 6.12.1), separate state key `rebar/prod/github.tfstate`, a `check` existence-gate over the deploy keys (fails loudly if S5's key absent). The `update` rule is the lock — it rejects direct pushes AND PR-merges for non-bypass actors.\n\n**Live apply-prove-rollback (proof):**\n1. terraform apply -> created gerrit-mirror-lock-main (18306896) + gerrit-mirror-lock-tags (18306898), both active.\n2. Deleted the pre-existing main-protection (18048287) -> lock is the sole governor.\n3. PROVED every non-bypass operation REJECTED (I am repo admin = non-bypass; only the DeployKey bypasses):\n   - direct `git push` to main -> `GH013 ... Cannot update this protected ref` (REJECTED).\n   - force-push to main -> REJECTED (GH013).\n   - PR-merge to main (PR #99, `gh pr merge --admin`) -> REJECTED (`Repository rule violations ... Cannot update this protected ref`).\n   - tag push -> REJECTED by the tag ruleset (GH013 for refs/tags/).\n   - main deletion -> REJECTED.\n   main HEAD unchanged by me (every proof push declined).\n4. ROLLED BACK: terraform destroy (both lock rulesets removed) + recreated main-protection from infra/github/main-protection.snapshot.json. Closed/deleted the proof PR + branch.\n5. VERIFIED final state == original: only `main-protection` active; its rules match the snapshot EXACTLY (deletion, non_fast_forward, pull_request, required_status_checks); no stray lock rulesets or proof tags on the remote.\n\n**AC mapping:** direct-push/PR-merge/force-push/deletion REJECTED (AC1) ✓; tag push REJECTED (AC2) ✓; native DeployKey bypass, sole bypass, idempotent (AC3) ✓; created active in a single terraform apply, no null_resource/gh-api-bypass/two-phase (AC4) ✓; deploy key obtained via data-source existence gate (AC5) ✓; main-protection replaced during the test, restored on rollback (AC6) ✓. Runbook: infra/runbooks/github-mirror-lock.md (cutover + <15min rollback). No secrets committed (token env/CI-sourced).\n\n**Code review (subagent):** VERDICT PASS — terraform correct, DeployKey bypass form correct, rollback whitelists create-time fields (no repo-destroy risk), no secrets, no perpetual diff. 2 NITs on the NON-default `--disable` rollback path (the proven default delete+recreate path needs no change)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1782814146281681001,"uuid":"a0a28476-7a53-4471-8b0e-666de719f424"}